window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>Sometimes, Rory Rutherford smells like candy. Usually, he smells like freshly baked bread, but such is the life of a baker. It was no accident Rory was in the park that day, but he couldn’t have foreseen what would transpire by the fountain.</p> <p>The breadcrumbs. The bird. The cat. Him. </p> <p>The guy Rory watches running past every Friday. The one who makes his heart beat fast and his hands feel sweaty. Nicky Costa. The Nick Costa–half-owner of Costa’s Italian Restaurant–the one they own—the family. And he’s sticking Band-Aids on Rory’s arm one minute and showing up at his workplace the next.</p> <p>Enjoy this sweet and sexy whirlwind romance set in the food industry and organized crime backdrops, but beware—do not listen on an empty stomach.</p>"; 
